parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake actuator can cause the vehicle to accelerate unexpectedly, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The "Check VSC System" warning light comes on
the vehicle accelerates unexpectedly
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal sticks to the floor
the vehicle lurches forward when hitting bumps or potholes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates unexpectedly
the vehicle surges forward when applying the brakes
the vehicle lurches forward when hitting bumps or potholes
the accelerator pedal sticks or feels soft.
